The paper deals with the conversion of fuzzy regular expressions into fuzzy automata, which falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures for the conversion process, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper proposes a new approach for the conversion process, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also involves dealing with uncertainty, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves mathematical concepts and proofs, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
